All forms used by the BaseSchema printing module are refered to by their superclass
form, for example the "CnEcReportEditForm" is a subclass of "CnEcReportEditSuper".
To invoke any of the printing module forms, use the global.cnEcGetReportModuleForm
method to return the appropriate Form subclass and create the superclass form as
the returned Form class, for example:

doPrintReport(pIsPreview:Boolean) updating, protected;

vars
	queueForm : CnEcReportQueueEntrySuper;

begin
	create queueForm as global.cnEcGetReportModuleForm(CnEcReportQueueEntrySuper);
	queueForm.setMyReport(cmbReport.listObject.CnEcReportDefinition);
	queueForm.setIsSchedule(false);		// False means queue, not schedule.
	queueForm.setIsPreview(pIsPreview);
	queueForm.showModal;
end;

If the superclass forms are subclassed, for example with the intention of replacing
the BaseSchema forms in favour of JUICE'd forms, then the global.cnEcGetReportModuleForm
method should be reimplemented in the application subschema to return the appropriate
Form class for the requested superclass Form.

Refer to the CnEcReportTestForm and the BaseReportTest application for an example of
instantiating Reporting forms.</text>
